    },
    "text_2": {
      "type": "content-block",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_1": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "A Swing at Style: Jason Day x Malbon",
            "tag": "h2",
            "size": "h3",
            "font": "serif"
          }
        },
        "text_1": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Jason Day's recent partnership with Malbon has made one thing clear: golf fashion is entering a new era and it's a little more street, a little more self-expressive, and a lot more interesting. Day's new on-course looks are far from the tucked-in, safe-zone polos of the past. Instead, we're seeing cropped silhouettes, bold graphics, and details that feel more runway than range.</p><p>It's rare for a top-tier athlete in such a tradition-heavy sport to fully lean into a fashion-forward brand. But that's exactly what Day is doing. He's not just wearing Malbon, he's embodying it. Confidently. Intentionally. With the kind of presence that makes you question why golf style has played it so safe for so long.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "heading_1",
        "text_1"
      ],
      "settings": {
        "alignment": "left",
        "enable_animation": true
      }
    },
