    "text_3": {
      "type": "content-block",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_1": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Why It Matters",
            "tag": "h2",
            "size": "h3",
            "font": "serif"
          }
        },
        "text_1": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Let's not underestimate this shift. Jason Day isn't a fringe player trying to get noticed through clothing, he's a former World No. 1, a PGA Champion, and one of the most respected guys on Tour. His decision to show up in wide-legged pants, graphic vests, and asymmetrical cuts sends a message: you can perform at the highest level and still look like <em>yourself</em>.</p><p>That's powerful. Not just for golf fashion, but for the next generation of players who want to bring their whole identity (style included) to the course.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "heading_1",
        "text_1"
      ],
      "settings": {
        "alignment": "left",
        "enable_animation": true
      }
    },
