    "text_4": {
      "type": "content-block",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_1": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Golf's Streetwear Crossover Is Just Beginning",
            "tag": "h2",
            "size": "h3",
            "font": "serif"
          }
        },
        "text_1": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Day isn't alone in this movement, but he's arguably the most high-profile face of it right now. And let's be honest, it's long overdue. The lines between golfwear and streetwear are blurring, and brands like Malbon are leading the charge. What used to be considered \"too casual\" for the clubhouse is quickly becoming the new standard for what's fresh, relevant, and wearable both on and off the course.</p><p>Whether you're a single-digit handicap or just here for the vibe, this evolution opens the door to make golf style something <em>personal</em>, not prescriptive.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "heading_1",
        "text_1"
